-- HSBC Sells A$5.9 Million of Discount Uridashi Notes
-- B y   H a r u m i   I c h i k u r a
-- 2012-03-13T16:12:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-13/hsbc-sells-a-5-9-million-of-discount-uridashi-notes.html
The following uridashi bond went
on sale. Uridashi bonds are debt issued in the euromarket
and sold mainly to Japanese individual investors.  Issuer:            HSBC Bank plc
Amount:            A$5.9 million
Coupon:            0.50 percent of face value
Issue Price:       57.10 percent of face value
Duration:          11 years
Sales period:      March 13 - March 30
Settlement date:   April 3, 2012
Maturity:          April 3, 2023
Uridashi Manager:  Akatsuki Securities Inc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Harumi Ichikura in London at   hichikura@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  